Following the violent clash between youth groups in Bauchi State resulting in the death of one person and others injured, the Bauchi State government have imposed a 24 hours curfew on the Yelwa community, a suburb of the Bauchi metropolis. This was contained in a press statement, issued and signed by the Chief of Staff, Government House, Aminu Hassan Gamawa and made available to newsmen in Bauchi. He said that the government has ordered a full investigation into the immediate and remote causes of the disturbance, adding that those found culpable will be dealt with, according to the law, -Advertisement- According to the statement, already, the security agencies have made some arrest. “It could be recalled that in the evening hours of Friday, the 27th day of May 2022, some miscreants in Yelwa and it’s environs in Bauchi local government, took laws into thier hands and embarked on looting properties, burning houses, cars and attacking innocent citizens for reasons under investigation by the authority” “In view of the foregoing, a 24 hour curfew is hereby imposed in Yelwa and it’s environs, especially Lushi, Tsakani, Kagadama and Birshi area of Bauchi local government.This action is not intended to cause hardship to the people, but to ensure the restoration of peace and order.The timings for the curfew will be reviewed from time to time as peace returns” “The government wishes to appreciate and thank the security agencies, traditional institutions, religious bodies and every law-abiding citizen of Bauchi state for their various roles in containing this crisis and ensuring peace across the state” The statement read in parts Daily Independent reports that the development is coming less than a month that the government imposed a curfew on communities around the Bauchi metropolis after that of Gudun Hausa in the month April .